    [div style="
    margin:0 auto; 
    background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.85); 
    width:100%; 
    padding:5px; 
    border-radius:15px;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);
    border:3px ridge #F7D58B;"][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img][/div][div id="section-role" style="
        font-size:25px;
        font-family:Garamond, serif;
        font-weight:bold; 
        color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;"]Prologue[/div]
        [div style="
        margin:10px auto;
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"] [div style="
        font-size:20px; 
        color: #cea425; 
        text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]The Paladin's Role[/div]
                [url=#section-prologue style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
        [div align="left"][size=25]T[/size]he Paladin stands at the forefront of battle, protecting allies by absorbing attacks and keeping enemies focused on them. With strong defense, mastery of shield blocking, and effective tools for managing and maintaining aggro, they ensure their team’s safety against any threat.

            [color=#cea425][b]Key Strengths:[/b][/color]  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Exceptional Defense:[/color] High shield block rate and damage mitigation keep the Paladin durable on the frontlines.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Strong Aggro Control:[/color] Reliable tools for maintaining enemy focus on both single targets and groups.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Self-Sustain:[/color] [color=#7fe07f]Healing[/color] enhanced by [color=#e5d522]Majesty[/color] reduces reliance on party healers.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Team-Oriented Play:[/color] Protects teammates by mitigating damage and reducing pressure on healers.

            [color=#cea425][b]Challenges:[/b][/color]  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Aggro Management Practice:[/color] Maintaining [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] through proper rotation of [color=#e5d522]Job Abilities[/color] and [color=#00ffd0]Spells[/color] requires experience and timing.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Positioning Awareness:[/color] Optimal positioning is key for effective shield blocking and AoE [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] control.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Equipment Dependency:[/color] The Paladin's performance heavily relies on using gear optimized for specific situations.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Skill Mastery:[/color] Requires a good grasp of [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] mechanics, cooldown timings, and sub-job synergies.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Leadership and Knowledge:[/color] A solid understanding of events, objectives, and strategies is essential, as Paladins often lead the group and initiate pulls.

            [color=#cea425][b]Role Versatility:[/b][/color]  
            With their versatility and powerful [color=#F7D58B]Defensive capabilities[/color], Paladins excel in various situations.  
            They are the best tank for [color=#F7D58B]Dynamis Divergence[/color] and other content featuring physical damage bosses, while also being capable of mitigating magical damage when a [color=#F7D58B]Rune Fencer[/color] is unavailable.[/div][/div][/div]

        [div id="section-subjob" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0;
            text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]Sub-Job[/div]
                [url=#section-prologue style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]
            
            [div style="text-align:left"]
                        The choice of sub-job for a [color=#F7D58B]Paladin[/color] depends on the content and your role in the group. While [color=#F7D58B]Blue Mage[/color] dominates as the most versatile and universally effective sub-job, others like [color=#F7D58B]Rune Fencer[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]Scholar[/color] offer situational advantages in niche scenarios. Below is an analysis of the most popular [color=#F7D58B]Sub-Jobs[/color], highlighting their strengths, weaknesses, and practical usage.[/div]
            
            [table style="width:100%; border:3px ridge #b08d57; font-size:12px;"]
                [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                    [th colspan="4" style="color:#30230e; text-align:center; font-size:16px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold;"]Top Tier[/th]
                [/tr]


                [tr style="background-color:#333333;"]
                    [th style="color:#ffd700; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Sub-Job[/th]
                    [th style="color:#ffd700; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Strengths[/th]
                    [th style="color:#ffd700; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Weaknesses[/th]
                    [th style="color:#ffd700; text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Usage[/th]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; min-height:120px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1);"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/MBRDSOd.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Blue Mage[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Best for most content; excels in versatile situations.
                    
                    • High defense with [color=#00ffd0]Cocoon[/color] (+50% DEF) and versatile AoE enmity tools ([color=#00ffd0]Sheep Song[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color]).[/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Needs proper Blue Mage spell setup.

                    • Lower offensive output than other sub-jobs.[/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Versatile: Tanking, AoE pulls, and endgame content.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333;"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/M48LBoB.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Rune Fencer[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Generates strong enmity with [color=#00ffd0]Foil[/color], [color=#e5d522]Valiance[/color], and [color=#e5d522]Vallation[/color]. Lacks precise AoE tools, making it less ideal than [color=#F7D58B]Sub Blue[/color] for multitarget tanking.
                        
                        • Excels in magical defense with [color=#e5d522]Runes[/color], [color=#e5d522]Pflug[/color], and [color=#00ffd0]Barspells[/color].  
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Relies on [color=#00ffd0]Banishga[/color] for AoE pulls, lacking dedicated AoE tools.
                        
                        • No access to [color=#00ffd0]Cocoon[/color], resulting in weaker physical defense than Blue Mage.
                        
                        • Requires Master Level 45+ to access [color=#00ffd0]Foil[/color].
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Effective for both magical and physical tanking; excels in magic-heavy or niche fights.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                    [th colspan="4" style="color:#30230e; text-align:center; font-size:16px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold;"]Mid Tier[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; solid rgba(0,0,0,1);"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/FWXf6Vb.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Scholar[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Key for Aminon runs: AoE buffs ([color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Regen III[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Aquaveil[/color]) via [color=#e5d522]Light Arts[/color] and [color=#e5d522]Accession[/color].
                        
                        • Utility: [color=#00ffd0]Stoneskin[/color] for buff mitigation, AoE [color=#00ffd0]Sneak[/color]/[color=#00ffd0]Invisible[/color] for group movement.
                        
                        • [color=#e5d522]Sublimation[/color] ensures MP recovery for long fights.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Situational, mainly for Aminon encounters.
                        
                        • No enmity tools; relies on Paladin’s abilities.
                        
                        • Focused on group support over tanking.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Best for Aminon or heavy group support with AoE utility.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; solid rgba(0,0,0,1);"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/qQBSdaY.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Red Mage[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Used for AoE XP farming at [color=#ffd700]Crawler's Nest [S][/color].
                        
                        • Offers [color=#00ffd0]Aeolian Edge[/color] for AoE damage.
                        
                        • Self-buffs with [color=#00ffd0]Haste[/color] and [color=#00ffd0]Refresh[/color].
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Niche use; unsuitable for most endgame content.
                        
                        • Lacks tanking tools and group utility.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Solo AoE XP farming.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444;"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/5mCKggF.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Warrior[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Decent alternative to Blue Mage for tanking and DPS.
                        
                        • [color=#e5d522]Provoke[/color], [color=#e5d522]Berserk[/color], and [color=#e5d522]Warcry[/color] boost enmity and offense.
                        
                        • Works well in simple or DPS-focused content.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Weaker than Blue Mage in enmity and survivability.
                        
                        • Lacks magical defense and AoE enmity tools.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Suitable for general content, casual tanking, or extra DPS.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                    [th colspan="4" style="color:#30230e; text-align:center; font-size:16px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold;"]Low Tier[/th]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; solid rgba(0,0,0,1);"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/fSNCvMy.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Dark Knight[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Boosts DPS with [color=#e5d522]Souleater[/color] and [color=#e5d522]Last Resort[/color].
                        
                        • [color=#00ffd0]Stun[/color] interrupts enemy abilities.
                        
                        • Aids enmity generation in short fights.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Outperformed by Blue Mage in tanking and enmity.
                        
                        • Trades survivability for minor offensive gains.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]DPS boost or interrupt utility in niche scenarios.[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333;"]
                    [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/PLWWs3y.png[/img]
                        [color=#F7D58B]Dancer[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Previously favored for casual solo play with [color=#e5d522]Waltzes[/color] for self-healing.
                        
                        • Offers utility via [color=#e5d522]Sambas[/color] (e.g., Drain Samba).
                        
                        • Still has niche applications for farming.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:left; padding:5px; solid rgba(0,0,0,1); border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]• Rarely used; lacks enmity tools and group utility.
                        
                        • Weaker survivability than other sub-jobs.
                    [/td]
                    [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px; border:1px ridge #b08d57;"]Casual solo play or farming (if still used).[/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table][/div]
        
