        [div id="section-atonement-mechanics" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            line-height:1.5;
            text-align:left;"]
            [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Atonement Mechanics[/color]
                [url=#section-enmity-main style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url][/div]
            
            [color=#cea425][b]Enmity Damage Formula Explained[/b][/color]
            • (([color=#ff9966]CE ÷ 6[/color]) - 1) + (([color=#ff7f50]VE ÷ 6[/color]) - 1)  

            [color=#cea425][b]Key Mechanics:[/b][/color]  
            • The [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] multiplier ([color=#F7D58B]fTP mod[/color]) is capped at [color=#F7D58B]x3[/color] when reaching [color=#e5d522]3000 TP[/color].  
            • Additional TP bonuses (like gorgets or belts) do not increase the cap beyond [color=#F7D58B]x3[/color].  

            [color=#cea425][b]Gear Bonuses:[/b][/color]  
            • Certain gear, such as R15 [color=#66ccff]Burtgang[/color], enhances the multiplier, but it cannot exceed the maximum [color=#F7D58B]x3[/color].

            [color=#cea425][b]Important Notes and Tips:[/b][/color]  
            • Maximize your [color=#ff7f50]CE[/color] and [color=#ffa07a]VE[/color] to ensure higher damage output from enmity-based mechanics.  
            • Focus on gear with [color=#ffb380]Enmity+[/color] bonuses and specific multipliers to optimize efficiency.  
            • Remember that while gear improves the output, the hard cap of [color=#F7D58B]x3[/color] cannot be bypassed.
