        [div id="section-enmity-generation-overview" style="
        margin:10px auto; 
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
        color:#E0E0E0; 
        font-size:14px;
        line-height:1.5;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Enmity Generation[/color]
                [url=#section-enmity-main style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]
            
            [color=#cea425][b]Understanding Enmity Generation[/b][/color]  
            [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] generation in combat is influenced by two main factors: the [color=#F7D58B]Base Value[/color] of an action and the [color=#F7D58B]Total Modifier[/color] applied through gear and buffs. Balancing these factors is essential for managing threat and maintaining control in battle.

            [color=#cea425][b]Formula Overview:[/b][/color]  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Base Value[/color]: Defined by the action, divided into [color=#ffa07a]Volatile Enmity (VE)[/color] and [color=#ffa366]Cumulative Enmity (CE)[/color].  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Final Enmity[/color] = Base Enmity × Total Modifier  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Total Modifier[/color]: Derived from:  
            • [color=#66ccff]Equipment Bonus[/color]: Enmity gained from gear (e.g., [color=#ff7f50]+159%[/color] with the [color=#66ccff]Full Enmity Set[/color]).  
            • [color=#00ffd0]Crusade Buff[/color]: Additional [color=#ff7f50]+30%[/color] enmity from the [color=#00ffd0]Crusade[/color] spell.  

            [color=#cea425][b]Example Calculation:[/b][/color]  
            An action with [color=#ffa07a]1,000 VE[/color] using the [color=#66ccff]Full Enmity Set[/color] ([color=#ff7f50]+159%[/color]) and [color=#00ffd0]Crusade[/color] ([color=#ff7f50]+30%[/color]):  
            [color=#ffa07a]1,000 VE[/color] × ([color=#ffa07a]1[/color] + [color=#ffa07a]1.59[/color] + [color=#ffa07a]0.30[/color]) = [color=#ffa07a]2,890 VE[/color].

            [div align="center"][table style="width:100%; border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); font-size:12px;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1A;"]
