        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
        color:#E0E0E0; 
        font-size:14px;
        line-height:1.5;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Basic Principles of Effective Aggro Generation[/color]
                [url=#section-enmity-main style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]
            
            [size=14][color=#E0E0E0]Managing [color=#ff7f50]Aggro[/color] effectively is the cornerstone of a [color=#F7D58B]Paladin's[/color] role in any combat scenario.  
                Ensuring that enemies focus their attacks on you and not on vulnerable party members requires a strategic balance of [color=#00ffd0]Spells[/color], [color=#e5d522]Job Abilities (JAs)[/color], and gear.  

                This section provides a foundational guide on how to generate and maintain [color=#ff7f50]Aggro[/color] using single-target and AoE strategies.
                By mastering these principles, you will not only solidify your position as the primary tank but also ensure your party’s safety and efficiency during encounters.  

                Whether dealing with single targets or multiple enemies, understanding the nuances of [color=#ffa07a]Volatile Enmity (VE)[/color] and [color=#ffa366]Cumulative Enmity (CE)[/color] will make you a more reliable and effective tank.[/color][/size]
            [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="4"]Single Target Priority[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"]Action[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"]Objective[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"][color=#ffa07a]VE[/color] Generated[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"][color=#ffa366]CE[/color] Generated[/th]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Divine Emblem[/color] + [color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Initial aggro spike to quickly add yourself to the hate list.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa07a]4202[/color] (with Chevalier's Sabatons +3)[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa366]591[/color][/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] + [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color] or [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Boost [color=#ff7f50]Enmity+[/color] with [color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] and deliver a significant spike using [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color] or [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color].[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]3456[/color] / [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]614[/color] per member affected[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color]: [color=#ffa366]1728[/color] / [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color]: [color=#ffa366]614[/color] per member affected[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Shield Bash[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Maintain aggro while delivering a solid VE/CE spike.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa07a]1728[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa366]864[/color][/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color] or [color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Maintain steady aggro while delivering consistent spikes of [color=#ffa07a]VE[/color] and [color=#ffa366]CE[/color].[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]2457[/color] / [color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]1966[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa366]345 CE[/color][/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Blank Gaze → Geist Wall → Sheep Song[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Alternate to maintain aggro while waiting for cooldowns.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Each generates [color=#ffa07a]464 VE[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Each generates [color=#ffa366]464 CE[/color][/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="4"]Multiple Target Priority[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"]Action[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"]Objective[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"][color=#ffa07a]VE[/color] Generated[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color: #ffd700;"][color=#ffa366]CE[/color] Generated[/th]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Sheep Song[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Geist Wall[/color], or [color=#00ffd0]Cold Wave[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Open with an [color=#00ffd0]AoE spell[/color] to ensure all enemies are aware of your presence and add you to their hate lists.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa07a]464 VE[/color] per target[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa366]464 CE[/color] per target[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] + [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color] or [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Boost [color=#ff7f50]Enmity+[/color] with [color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] and deliver a significant spike using [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color] or [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color].[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]3456[/color] / [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color]: [color=#ffa07a]614[/color] per member affected[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color]: [color=#ffa366]1728[/color] / [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color]: [color=#ffa366]614[/color] per member affected[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Supplement your aggro generation with a conal AoE spike. Ensure proper positioning to avoid unintended targets.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa07a]1966 VE[/color] total[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#ffa366]345 CE[/color] total[/td]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#00ffd0]Sheep Song → Geist Wall → Cold Wave[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Rotate between these spells to maintain aggro while waiting for cooldowns.[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Each generates [color=#ffa07a]464 VE[/color] per target[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Each generates [color=#ffa366]464 CE[/color] per target[/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table][/div]

            [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
                border-collapse: collapse;
                font-size: 12px;
                padding: 5px;
                margin: 15px 0;
                line-height:1.5;
                box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                border-radius: 10px;
                overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#222222; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="2"]General Tips for Both Single and AoE Scenarios[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Ability Alignment[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Maximize the impact of [color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color], [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color], and [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color] by timing their usage during high-pressure moments. Avoid overlapping them unless necessary to maintain consistent mitigation and aggro generation.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Adaptability[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Always consider encounter-specific mechanics, such as aggro resets, waves of adds, or high-damage phases. Adjust your rotation dynamically to meet the fight's demands.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Cooldown Management[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Rotate abilities effectively to avoid periods of inactivity. Fill downtime with spells like [color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color] or AoE options ([color=#00ffd0]Sheep Song[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Geist Wall[/color], etc.).[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#222222; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="2"]Single Target Specifics[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Opening Sequence[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Begin with [color=#e5d522]Divine Emblem[/color] + [color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color] to establish a strong presence on the hate list. Follow with [color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] + [color=#e5d522]Palisade[/color] or [color=#e5d522]Rampart[/color].[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Shield Bash[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Use [color=#e5d522]Shield Bash[/color] to maintain aggro and deliver a significant spike in [color=#ffa07a]VE[/color] and [color=#ffa366]CE[/color].[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Aggro Maintenance[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Rotate [color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color] and [color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color] to sustain consistent enmity, ensuring cooldowns are utilized efficiently.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#222222; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="2"]AoE Specifics[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Sentinel Usage[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Pair [color=#e5d522]Sentinel[/color] with AoE abilities for maximum [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] impact across multiple targets.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Spell Rotation[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Rotate between [color=#00ffd0]Sheep Song[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Geist Wall[/color], and [color=#00ffd0]Cold Wave[/color] to maintain enmity on all targets.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#222222; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:16px;" colspan="2"]Fight-Specific Adjustments[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Mechanics Awareness[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Plan ability usage around fight mechanics like aggro resets, spawn timings, or targeted phases.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Team Coordination[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Communicate with your party to ensure synchronized cooldowns for optimal mitigation and damage distribution.[/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table][/div][/div]
    [/div]

    [div style="
    margin:25px auto; 
    background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.85); 
    width:100%; 
    padding:5px; 
    border-radius:15px; 
    border:2px ridge rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); 
    box-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(244, 228, 142, 0.8), 0 0 5px rgba(255, 223, 0, 0.6) inset;"][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img][/div]
        [div id="section-damage-taken" style="
        font-size:30px; 
        font-weight:bold; 
        color:#ffd700; 
        text-shadow: 0px 0px 5px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 10px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 15px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5);"]DEFENSE[/div]
            [url=#section-defense style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]

            [div id="section-damage-reduction" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            line-height:1.5;
            text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Damage Taken Reduction Mechanics[/color]
            [url=#section-defense style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url][/div]

            [color=#F7D58B]Damage Taken (DT):[/color]
            • A global reduction applied to all types of damage.  
            • Maximum cap: [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color].  
            • Reduces all damage before applying specific reductions (e.g., [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color]).  

            [color=#F7D58B]Physical Damage Taken (PDT):[/color]
            • Applies only to physical attacks.  
            • Cap: [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color], extendable with [color=#F7D58B]PDT II[/color].  
            • [color=#F7D58B]PDT II[/color] (e.g., [color=#66ccff]Burtgang[/color]) allows reductions beyond the standard limit.  

            [color=#F7D58B]Magical Damage Taken (MDT):[/color]
            • Specific to magical attacks.  
            • Cap: [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color], extendable with [color=#F7D58B]MDT II[/color].  
            • Tools like [color=#66ccff]Aegis[/color] extend reductions up to [color=#F7D58B]-87.5%[/color].  

            [color=#F7D58B]Advanced Reductions:[/color]
            • Special tools like [color=#66ccff]Burtgang[/color] or [color=#66ccff]Aegis[/color] allow surpassing conventional caps.  
            • These reductions are critical for mitigating extreme damage scenarios.  

            [table style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]Type[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]Cap[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]Formula[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]Notes[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#F7D58B]Damage Taken (DT):[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]-50%[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Applies to all damage types[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"]Combines with [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color], or [color=#F7D58B]BDT[/color] to reach their caps.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#F7D58B]Physical Damage Taken (PDT):[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]-50%[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"](Uncorrected Damage) × (100% - PDT - DT)[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"]Use [color=#66ccff]Burtgang[/color] ([color=#F7D58B]-18% PDT II[/color]) to exceed cap; reduces to [color=#F7D58B]32%[/color].[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#F7D58B]Magical Damage Taken (MDT):[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]-50%[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Floor((Magic Damage) × (100% - [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] - [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color])) ÷ (1 + [color=#F7D58B]MDB[/color] ÷ 100)[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"]Use [color=#66ccff]Aegis[/color] ([color=#F7D58B]-50% MDT II[/color]) for up to [color=#F7D58B]87.5%[/color] reduction.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#F7D58B]Breath Damage Taken (BDT):[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]-50%[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"](Breath Base Damage) × (1 - [color=#F7D58B]BDT[/color] - [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] - [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] augmentations)[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"]Gear with [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] augments helps reduce breath damage.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"][color=#F7D58B]PDT II/MDT II:[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Up to -87.5%[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center;"]Special reductions beyond standard [color=#F7D58B]PDT/MDT[/color] caps[/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"]Examples: [color=#66ccff]Burtgang[/color] ([color=#F7D58B]PDT II[/color]), [color=#66ccff]Aegis[/color] ([color=#F7D58B]MDT II[/color]).[/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [table style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            width: 100%;"]
                [tr style="background-color: #333333; color: #E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; color: #ffd700;"]Example[/th]
                    [th style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; color: #ffd700;"]Details[/th]
                    [th style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; color: #ffd700;"]Corrected Damage[/th]
                    [th style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; color: #ffd700;"]Explanation[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color: #444444; color: #E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Physics[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]-50% [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color]  
                        -18% [color=#F7D58B]PDT II[/color]
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]1000 × (1 - 0.50 - 0.18)  
                        320 damage taken
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color] caps at [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color], but [color=#F7D58B]PDT II[/color] allows reductions beyond the cap.  
                        This results in further reduced physical damage.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color: #333333; color: #E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Magics[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]-50% [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color]  
                        -50% [color=#F7D58B]MDT II[/color]  
                        [color=#F7D58B]MDB[/color] +20
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]Floor((1000 × (1 - 0.50 - 0.375)) ÷ (1 + 20 ÷ 100))  
                        104 damage taken
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] reduces by [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color] initially.  
                        [color=#F7D58B]MDT II[/color] adds [color=#F7D58B]-37.5%[/color], reaching the cap of [color=#F7D58B]-87.5%[/color].  
                        [color=#F7D58B]MDB[/color] further divides the remaining damage by its bonus percentage.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color: #444444; color: #E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Breaths[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]-50% [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color]  
                        -30% [color=#F7D58B]BDT[/color]  
                        -10% [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] augmentations
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"]1000 × (1 - 0.50)  
                        500 damage taken
                    [/td]
                    [td style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;"][color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] already caps at [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color], applying globally to all damage types.  
                        Contributions from [color=#F7D58B]BDT[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] are not applied further.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table][/div]
        
        [div id="section-physicals-resistances" style="
        margin:10px auto; 
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
        color:#E0E0E0; 
        font-size:14px;
        line-height:1.5;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Physical Damage Mitigation[/color]
                [url=#section-defense style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]

            [size=14 style="line-height:1.5; color:#E0E0E0;"]Optimizing [color=#F7D58B]Physical Damage Mitigation[/color] for a Paladin involves careful management of [color=#F7D58B]DEF[/color], [color=#F7D58B]Shield Mechanics[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]Critical Hit Mitigation[/color]. Below is a structured summary:
            [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Defense (DEF)[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Description[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Base DEF[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Calculated using level and Vitality (VIT).  
                    Formula: [i]Base DEF = floor(VIT × 1.5) + level adjustment[/i][/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Equipment DEF[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Direct addition of DEF values from equipment.[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Active Buffs[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#00ffd0]Protect V[/color]: Adds 220 DEF (+ shield DEF when cast by Paladin).  
                    Example: Shield with 130 DEF results in a total of 350 DEF.  
                    
                    [color=#00ffd0]Cocoon[/color]: Boosts DEF by 50% (Blue Mage Spell).[/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Impact on Attack/DEF Ratio[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Favorable ratio reduces damage.  
                    Unfavorable ratio increases damage, mitigated by high DEF.[/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [table width="100%" style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Shield Mechanics[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:leftr; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Description[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Shield Skill Mechanics[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Shields block physical attacks from the front.  
                    Formula: BlockRate = BaseRate + ((ShieldSkill - AttackerSkill) × 0.2325).  
                    Example: Shield Skill 420 and BaseRate 45% → Block Rate = 49.65%.  
                    Ultimate Shields: Specific shields like Aegis ignore conventional rules.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Damage Reduction[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Formula: PercentDamageBlocked = SizeDamageReduction + (ShieldDEF / X).  
                    X varies depending on shield level:  
                    • Non-ilvl shields: ShieldDEF/2.  
                    • ilvl 119 shields: ShieldDEF/4.  
                    Final Damage Taken: BaseDamage × (1 - Reduction/100).  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Damage Reduction on Block[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Formula: FinalDamage = (BaseDamage - ShieldBonus) × (1 - BlockPercent/100).  
                    Example: 1000 damage, 60% reduction, and 30% PDT = 280 final damage.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Abilities[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Reprisal: Increases block rate by 50% (or 3x with Priwen).  
                    • Palisade: Adds 30% block rate (+20% merits), prevents hate loss on block.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Standard Shields[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 0 auto; /* Centrage horizontal */
                        line-height:1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Shield[/th]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Size[/th]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Total Damage Reduction[/th]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Base Block Rate[/th]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/d/db/Dynamis_Shield_icon.png[/img]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]1[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-20%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]55%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/1/12/Chef%27s_Ecu_icon.png[/img]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]2[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-40%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]40%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/9/9d/Jennet_Shield_icon.png[/img]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]3[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-50%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]45%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/1/18/Scutum_icon.png[/img]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]4[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-65%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]30%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                    [/table][/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Ultimate Shields[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 0 auto; /* Centrage horizontal */
                        line-height:1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Shield[/th]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Total Damage Reduction[/th]
                            [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Base Block Rate[/th]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/c/c2/Aegis_%28Level_75%29_icon.png[/img]
                            Aegis[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-75%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]50%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/1/1c/Srivatsa_icon.png[/img]
                            Srivatsa[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-75%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]50%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/a/a2/Ochain_%28Level_85%29_icon.png[/img]
                            Ochain[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-60%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]~108%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                        [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://www.bg-wiki.com/images/a/ab/Duban_%28Incomplete%29_icon.png[/img]
                            Duban[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]-60%[/td]
                            [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]~108%[/td]
                        [/tr]
                    [/table][/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [table width="100%" style="
                border-collapse: collapse;
                font-size: 12px;
                padding: 5px;
                margin: 15px 0;
                line-height:1.5;
                box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                border-radius: 10px;
                overflow: hidden;"]
                [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Enemy Critical Hit Rate[/th]
                [/tr]

                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                    [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Details[/th]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Critical Hit Rate Reduction[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Enemy critical hit rate[/color] is a merit category available to all jobs. Each merit upgrade grants a 1% reduction in critical hit rate from enemies, up to a maximum of 5% reduction.  
                    This costs 15 merits for a full upgrade (1 > 2 > 3 > 4 > 5).  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Critical Hit Rate Formula[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Enemy critical hit rate[/color] seems to be calculated similarly to Player Critical Hit Rate, but uses the Enemy's DEX and the Player's AGI.  
                    • Higher AGI reduces the Enemy's critical hit rate.  
                    • Minimum critical hit rate: 1%.  
                    • Cap on [color=#F7D58B]Enemy critical hit rate[/color]: 10% (exceptions apply).  
                    • To reduce a capped 10% critical hit rate to the minimum of 1%, 9% reduction is required.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Reduction Calculation[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Example:  
                    • Merits (5/5): -5%.  
                    • Fortified Ring: -7%.  
                    Total reduction = 12%, reducing 10% to 1%.  
                    Avoid overcapping by carefully balancing gear and merits.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Recommended Equipment[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• [color=#66ccff]Warden's Ring[/color]: Enemy critical hit rate -5%, "Death" resistance +10, Physical damage taken -3%.  
                    • [color=#66ccff]Eluder's Sachet[/color]: Enemy critical hit rate -5%, Damage taken +2%.  
                    • [color=#66ccff]Fortified Ring[/color]: Enemy critical hit rate -7%, MP+50, Accuracy+5, Magic damage taken -5%.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
                [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Importance for Tanks[/color][/td]
                    [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]Tanks can reduce the spike damage from critical hits by equipping items with Enemy critical hit rate reduction.  
                    • Particularly useful in situations with [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color], where overall damage can approach zero.  
                    • Focus on reducing critical hit spikes for greater stability.  
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table][/div][/div]

        [div id="section-magics-resistances" style="
        margin:10px auto; 
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
        color:#E0E0E0; 
        font-size:14px;
        line-height:1.5;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Magical Damage Mitigation[/color]
                [url=#section-defense style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]

            [size=14 style="line-height:1.5; color:#E0E0E0;"]Optimizing [color=#F7D58B]Magical Damage Mitigation[/color] for a Paladin involves careful management of [color=#F7D58B]Magic Evasion (Meva)[/color], [color=#F7D58B]Elemental Resistance[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]Magic Defense Bonus (MDB)[/color]. Below is a structured summary:
            [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
                border-collapse: collapse;
                font-size: 12px;
                padding: 5px;
                margin: 15px 0;
                line-height:1.5;
                box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                border-radius: 10px;
                overflow: hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Magic Evasion[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Description[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Core Mechanics[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Magic Evasion is compared to attacker's Magic Accuracy
                            • +2 Magic Evasion = +1% Resist (below 50%), +2% Resist (above 50%)[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]PLD Optimization[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Equipment like Sakpata's Plate maximizes Magic Evasion
                            • For optimal mitigation:
                                - Combine high Magic Evasion AND elemental resistance
                                - Prioritize gear providing both stats[/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table]
                [table width="100%" style="
                    border-collapse: collapse;
                    font-size: 12px;
                    padding: 5px;
                    margin: 15px 0;
                    line-height:1.5;
                    box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                    border-radius: 10px;
                    overflow: hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Elemental Resistance[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Description[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Importance and Scenarios[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Negative Resistance guarantees at least 1/2 damage
                            • Positive Resistance, with MEVA, enables full resist (1/8 damage)
                            • Bar-spells boost resistance for specific elemental threats[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Application for PLD[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• [color=#66ccff]Carrier's Sash[/color] offers broad elemental resistance
                            • [color=#66ccff]Warden's Charm[/color] / [color=#66ccff]+1[/color] helps manage multiple elemental resistances
                            • [color=#00ffd0]Bar-spells[/color] for specific vulnerabilities[/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table]
                [table width="100%" style="
                    border-collapse: collapse;
                    font-size: 12px;
                    padding: 5px;
                    margin: 15px 0;
                    line-height:1.5;
                    box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                    border-radius: 10px;
                    overflow: hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Magic Defense Bonus (MDB)[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Details[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]General Description[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Formula: Final Damage = Base Damage × (100 + MAB) ÷ (100 + MDB)
                            • Applies to all magical damage including Quick Draw and elemental WSs[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Limitations[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Does not affect breath attacks
                            • Same-tier traits do not stack
                            • No known cap[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Enemy Interaction[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Enemy MAB can exceed 900 in extreme cases
                            • Most enemies lack MDB except NMs[/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table]
                [table width="100%" style="
                    border-collapse: collapse;
                    font-size: 12px;
                    padding: 5px;
                    margin: 15px 0;
                    line-height:1.5;
                    box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                    border-radius: 10px;
                    overflow: hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Damage Calculation Order[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Step[/th]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Details[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]1. Magic Evasion[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Determines initial resist state:
                            • Full Hit → All damage
                            • Partial Resist → 1/2 or 1/4 damage
                            • Full Resist → 1/8 damage[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]2. Elemental Resistance[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Modifies resist state:
                            • Negative → Forces minimum 1/2 damage
                            • Positive → Enables full resists with MEVA[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]3. Magic Damage Taken[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Formula: Remaining = Base × (1 - MDT)
                            • Caps at 50% (87.5% with Aegis)[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]4. Magic Defense Bonus[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Final calculation using MDB formula
                            • Last layer of defense[/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table]
            [/div]
        [/div]

        [div id="section-phalanx" style="
        margin:10px auto; 
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
        color:#E0E0E0; 
        font-size:14px;
        line-height:1.5;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Phalanx Mechanics and Usage[/color]
                [url=#section-defense style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            [/div]

            [size=14 style="line-height:1.5; color:#E0E0E0;"][color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] is a powerful defensive enhancement that applies a flat damage reduction to incoming hits. This reduction occurs at the very end of all damage calculations, making it particularly effective at eliminating residual damage. With a well-optimized [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx Potency[/color] set, most incoming hits will be reduced to zero or negligible amounts, making it one of the [color=#F7D58B]Paladin's[/color] most powerful defensive tools.

            Once all other damage calculations are complete ([color=#ffb380]PDT[/color], [color=#ffb380]MDT[/color], resistances, etc.), [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] subtracts its fixed value from the remaining damage. Since many end-game hits are already heavily mitigated by your other defensive mechanics, [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] often represents the difference between taking small damage and no damage at all.

            [color=#cea425]Advanced Tip[/color]: When paired with a [color=#F7D58B]Red Mage[/color], you can combine the best of both jobs by synchronizing your [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] casts:
            • The [color=#F7D58B]PLD[/color] provides high potency from their gear set
            • The [color=#F7D58B]RDM[/color] contributes enhanced duration
            • Coordinate using a countdown "3, 2, 1" and cast simultaneously
            • Result: You get your potency with [color=#F7D58B]RDM's[/color] extended duration[/size]
            [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            line-height:1.5;
            box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Phalanx Mechanics[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Aspect[/th]
                        [th style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Description[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Core Mechanics[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] reduces damage by a fixed amount based on [color=#00ffd0]Enhancing Magic skill[/color]
                            [u][b]Damage reduction formula:[/b][/u]
                                • Up to 300 skill: Floor(Skill/10) - 2
                                • Over 300 skill: 28 + Floor((Skill - 300.5)/28.5)[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Equipment Bonus[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• [color=#66ccff]Phalanx+ gear bonuses[/color] directly add to damage reduction
                            • Equipment must be worn when receiving [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color]
                            • Effect persists even after gear swap[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Important Thresholds[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][table width="100%" style="
                            border-collapse: collapse;
                            font-size: 12px;
                            margin: 0 auto;
                            line-height:1.5;"]
                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]Skill Level[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]300[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]329[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]358[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]386[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]415[/th]
                                [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#ffd700;"]500[/th]
                            [/tr]
                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#d64848;"]Damage Reduction[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-28[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-29[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-30[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-31[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-32[/td]
                                [td style="padding:5px; text-align:center; color:#7fe07f;"]-35[/td]
                            [/tr]
                        [/table][/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Damage Calculation[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] reduction is applied after [color=#ffb380]Damage Taken[/color] equipment
                            • Example: 100 damage with [color=#00ffd0]Phalanx[/color] -20 becomes 80 damage[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][color=#F7D58B]Optimization Note[/color][/td]
                        [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]• Skills between tiers provide no additional benefit
                            • Example: 410 skill gives same reduction as 386 skill (-31)
                            • Plan gear and buffs to reach specific thresholds[/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table][/div][/div]
        [/div]

        [div style="
        margin:25px auto; 
        background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.85); 
        width:100%; 
        padding:5px; 
        border-radius:15px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); 
        box-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(244, 228, 142, 0.8), 0 0 5px rgba(255, 223, 0, 0.6) inset;"][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img][/div]
            [div id="section-gears-gearswap" style="font-size:26px; font-weight:bold; color:#ffd700; text-shadow: 0px 0px 5px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 10px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 15px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5);"]HP Management and Optimization
            [/div]
            [url=#section-equipment style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]

            [div id="section-magics-resistances" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            line-height:1.5;
            text-align:left;"]
                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px;"][color=#cea425]Using GearSwap: HP Management and Optimization[/color][/div]


                    [b][color=#F7D58B]Optimizing HP Management During Gear Swaps:[/color][/b]
                    Proper gear swapping is essential to maintain optimal HP during combat. The gear swap cycle differs depending on the action performed:

                    [b][color=#F7D58B]For Spells (Magic):[/color][/b]  
                    When casting a spell, the gear transition follows this cycle:
                    [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 15px 0;
                        line-height:1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]
                            [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Complete Casting Cycle for Magic Spells[/th]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; width:30%;"]Step[/th]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Explanation[/th]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Idle Phase[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]The character is in a neutral state, waiting for action.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Precast Phase[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]The moment when the spell is initiated, focusing on reducing casting time (Fast Cast effect).[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Midcast Phase[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]The spell is being cast. The spell's potency, duration, or accuracy is determined here.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Return to Idle[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]After the spell is completed, the character returns to the idle state, ready for the next action.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Visual Representation[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]
                                    [table style="
                                    border-collapse: collapse;
                                    font-size: 12px;
                                    margin: 0 auto;
                                    line-height:1.5;"]
                                        [tr]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Idle[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]→[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Precast[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]→[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Midcast[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]→[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Idle[/th]
                                        [/tr]
                                    [/table]
                                [/td]
                            [/tr]
                        [/table]
                    [/div]

                    [b][color=#F7D58B]For Job Abilities (JA):[/color][/b]
                    Job Abilities do not require a midcast phase. Their cycle is simpler:
                    [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 15px 0;
                        line-height:1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]

                            [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; font-size:20px;" colspan="2"]Complete Execution Cycle for Job Abilities (JA)[/th]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700; width:30%;"]Step[/th]
                                [th style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffd700;"]Explanation[/th]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Idle Phase[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]The character is in a neutral state, waiting to activate a Job Ability.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Execution Phase[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]The moment the Job Ability is activated, applying its effect instantly or after a short delay.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#444444; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Return to Idle[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:left; vertical-align:middle;"]After the ability is used, the character returns to the idle state, ready for the next action.[/td]
                            [/tr]

                            [tr style="background-color:#333333; color:#E0E0E0;"]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][b][color=#F7D58B]Visual Representation[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="padding:10px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"]
                                    [table style="
                                    border-collapse: collapse;
                                    font-size: 12px;
                                    margin: 0 auto;
                                    line-height:1.5;"]
                                        [tr]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Idle[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]→[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Execution[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]→[/th]
                                            [th style="padding:5px; text-align:center;"]Idle[/th]
                                        [/tr]
                                    [/table]
                                [/td]
                            [/tr]
                        [/table]
                    [/div]

                    [b][color=#F7D58B]GearSwap Optimization Impact on HP Stability:[/color][/b]  
                    The following tables illustrate the difference in HP management during combat when using GearSwap with proper priority settings versus without optimization.

                [div style="text-align:center; margin-top:20px;"][b][size=16][color=#cea425]With GearSwap Optimization (Minimized HP Loss)[/color][/size][/b][div align="center"][table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 15px 0;
                        line-height: 1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]
                            [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA;"]
                                [td style="width:45%; text-align:center; padding:5px;"][b][color=#cea425]Actual Set[/color][/b][/td]
                                [td style="width:10%; text-align:center; padding:5px;" colspan=3][/td][td style="width:45%; text-align:center; padding:5px;"][b][color=#cea425]Next Set[/color][/b][/td]
                            [/tr]
                            [tr style="background-color:#393939;"]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Idle Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]3182/3182 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;" colspan=3][size=20]→[/size]
                                    [color=green]-0 HP[/color]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Fast Cast Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]2938/2938 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                            [/tr]
                            [tr style="background-color:#444444;"]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Fast Cast Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]2938/2938 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;" colspan=3][size=20]→[/size]
                                    [color=orange]-53 HP[/color]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Full Enmity Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]2938/2991 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■[/color][color=#ffff00]■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                            [/tr]
                            [tr style="background-color:#393939;"]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Full Enmity Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]2938/2991 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■[/color][color=#ffff00]■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;" colspan=3][size=20]→[/size]
                                    [color=red]-244 HP[/color]
                                [/td]
                                [td style="text-align:center; padding:5px;"]Idle Set
                                    [color=#99ff99]2938/3182 HP[/color]
                                    [size=20][color=#00ff00]■■■■■■■■■[/color][color=#ff0000]■[/color][/size]
                                [/td]
                            [/tr]
                        [/table]

                        [b][size=16][color=#cea425]Without GearSwap Optimization (Significant HP Loss)[/color][/size][/b]
                        [table width="100%" style="
                        border-collapse: collapse;
                        font-size: 12px;
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin: 15px 0;
                        line-height: 1.5;
                        box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3), 0 0 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        border-radius: 10px;
                        overflow: hidden;"]
                            [tr style="background-color:#1A1A1ADA; color:#E0E0E0;"]
