                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Optimizing Without GearSwap: Aligning HP Across Sets[/color][/div]

                [size=14][color=#F7D58B][b]Why Align HP Across Gear Sets?[/b][/color][/size]
                [color=#ffffff]Swapping between sets with significant [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] differences can cause unintended HP drops, forcing unnecessary healing and wasting resources.

                    [size=14][color=#F7D58B][b][u]Common Issue[/u][/b][/color][/size]
                    • [b][color=#66ccff]Idle Set:[/color][/b] [b][color=#99ff99]3200 HP[/color][/b]  
                    • [b][color=#66ccff]Fast Cast Set:[/color][/b] [b][color=#99ff99]2800 HP[/color][/b]  

                    Swapping from Idle to Fast Cast drops your [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] to [b][color=#99ff99]2800[/color][/b]. Even after returning to Idle, your HP remains at [b][color=#99ff99]2800/3200[/color][/b], simulating missing health.

                    [size=14][color=#F7D58B][b][u]Recommended Solution[/u][/b][/color][/size]
                    [b][color=#99ff99]✔[/color][/b] Align your sets to minimize [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] differences.  
                    [b][color=#99ff99]✔[/color][/b] Keep HP variance within [b][color=#99ff99]200 HP[/color][/b] to prevent noticeable drops.

                    [size=14][color=#F7D58B][b][u]Adjusted Example[/u][/b][/color][/size]  
                    • [b][color=#66ccff]Idle Set:[/color][/b] [b][color=#99ff99]2900 HP[/color][/b]  
                    • [b][color=#66ccff]Fast Cast Set:[/color][/b] [b][color=#99ff99]2800 HP[/color][/b]  
                    • [b][color=#66ccff]Enmity Set:[/color][/b] [b][color=#99ff99]2900 HP[/color][/b]  

                    [b][color=#99ff99]Result:[/color][/b] Smooth transitions with minimal HP fluctuation, reducing healing needs and ensuring better survivability.[/color]
                
                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Conclusion: Adapt HP and Prioritize Intelligently[/color][/div]

                • [b][color=#F7D58B]With GearSwap:[/color][/b] Use priorities to manage the equip order and avoid visible [b][color=#99ff99]HP loss[/color][/b].
                • [b][color=#F7D58B]Without GearSwap:[/color][/b] Adjust your sets to limit [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] differences and maintain maximum stability.
                • Align your overall HP to the set with the lowest [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] (e.g., Fast Cast) to minimize variations.
                • Structure your transitions to avoid unnecessary [b][color=#99ff99]healing[/color][/b] cycles caused by apparent [b][color=#99ff99]HP gaps[/color][/b].

                Whether you use GearSwap or manual commands, these principles ensure optimized [b][color=#99ff99]HP[/color][/b] management and stable transitions during combat.
            [/div]
        [/div]

        [div style="margin:25px auto; background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.85); width:100%; padding:5px; border-radius:15px; border:2px ridge rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); box-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(244, 228, 142, 0.8), 0 0 5px rgba(255, 223, 0, 0.6) inset;"][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img]
            [/div]
            [div id="section-idle-pdt" style="font-size:26px; font-weight:bold; color:#ffd700; text-shadow: 0px 0px 5px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 10px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5), 0px 0px 15px rgba(253, 108, 0, 0.5);"]IDLE SETS[/div]
            [url=#section-idle-sets style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
            
            
            [div id="section-magics-resistances" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            line-height:1.5;
            text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Idle Set Overview[/color][/div]
                [color=#F7D58B][b]Idle Set[/b][/color] is designed to minimize damage when not actively performing actions.  
                It focuses on capping [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color],  
                while maintaining high [color=#F7D58B]DEF[/color], [color=#F7D58B]VIT[/color],  
                and a reasonable [color=#7fe07f]HP pool[/color] to avoid fluctuations during gear swaps.  

                [color=#cea425][b]Customization[/b][/color]  
                This setup can be adjusted with [color=#F7D58B]status resistance[/color]  
                and [color=#F7D58B]critical hit rate reduction[/color].  
                Boosting [color=#F7D58B]MEVA[/color], [color=#F7D58B]elemental resistances[/color],  
                and [color=#F7D58B]Magic Defense Bonus (MDB)[/color] enhances survivability against magic-based threats.  

                [color=#cea425][b]Conclusion[/b][/color]  
                The [color=#F7D58B][b]Idle Set[/b][/color] is essential for minimizing passive damage  
                and maintaining consistent defense, forming the foundation of any solid defensive strategy.
            [/div]

            [div id="section-idle-basic-pdt" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            text-align:left;"][div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Fresh 99 Basic Idle Set
                [url=#section-idle-sets style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url][/div][table][tr]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; line-height:2; font-size:14px; padding:10px;"]This is the most basic idle set designed for players who just reached level 99 on their first job ([b][color=#F7D58B]Paladin[/color][/b]).
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]No advanced content unlocked:[/color][/b] No access to [b][color=#66ccff]Reforged AF[/color][/b]/[b][color=#66ccff]Relic[/color][/b]/[b][color=#66ccff]Empyrean gear[/color][/b] or [b][color=#F7D58B]Ambuscade[/color][/b] yet.  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Very Limited Sources:[/color][/b] Gear primarily obtained through [b][color=#F7D58B]Sparks of Eminence[/color][/b] and [b][color=#F7D58B]Domain Points[/color][/b] only.
                            
                            [b][color=#F7D58B]Exceptions:[/color][/b]  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Creed Baudrier[/color][/b], obtained by defeating [b]Ironclad Executioner[/b] in [b]Abyssea - Vunkerl[/b].  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Charitoni Sling[/color][/b], obtained from the [b]Unity NM Prickly Pitriv[/b] in [b]East Sarutabaruta[/b].
                            
                            [b][color=#F7D58B]Sparks Gear Locations:[/color][/b]  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Rolandienne[/color][/b] in [b]Southern San d'Oria[/b] (G-10)  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Isakoth[/color][/b] in [b]Bastok Markets[/b] (E-11)  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Fhelm Jobeizat[/color][/b] in [b]Windurst Woods[/b] (J-10)  
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Eternal Flame[/color][/b] in [b]Western Adoulin[/b] (H-11)
                            
                            [b][color=#F7D58B]Domain Points Gear Location:[/color][/b]  
                            The [b][color=#66ccff]Sanctity Necklace[/color][/b] can be purchased from [b][color=#F7D58B]Zurim[/color][/b] in [b]Norg[/b] (I-7) – [b][color=#F7D58B]100 Domain Points[/color][/b].
                            
                            This set represents your very first defensive setup, providing just enough protection to help you start working towards better gear options.
                        [/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table][div align="center"][table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse; padding:5px; margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px; line-height:1.8; box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 12px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); border-radius:25px; overflow:hidden;"]
                        [tr style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);"][td style="text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; width:130px;"][itemset]397650[/itemset][/td]
                            [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; white-space:nowrap;"][div style="text-align:left; display:inline-block; line-height:1.5;"][size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]PDT: -17%[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]MDT: -7%[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Enmity: 11[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]VIT: 114[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]DEF: +831[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]HP: 366[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]MP: 84[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Evasion: 255[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Def. Bonus: 14%[/color][/b][/size]
                                [/div]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:0 10px 0 10px; vertical-align:middle;"][size=14]Basic defensive set built from [b][color=#F7D58B]Sparks[/color][/b]/[b][color=#F7D58B]Domain[/color][/b] gear, providing entry-level defensive capabilities for a fresh [b][color=#F7D58B]99 PLD[/color][/b].[/size]
                            [/td]
                        [/tr]
                    [/table][/div][/div]
            
            [div id="section-idle-low-pdt" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            text-align:left;"]
                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Low-Tier Idle Set[/color]
                    [url=#section-idle-sets style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
                [/div]
                [table]
                    [tr]
                        [td style="color:#ffffff; line-height:2; font-size:14px; padding:10px;"]This is a significant upgrade path designed for players who have moved beyond the basic Sparks/Domain Points gear.
                                
                            • [b][color=#F7D58B]Ambuscade Access:[/color][/b] Required for obtaining the full Sulevia's set.
                            • [b][color=#66ccff]Supershear Ring:[/color][/b] Dropped by [b][color=#F7D58B]Titan Prime[/color][/b] in [b][color=#F7D58B]★Trial by Earth[/color][/b]. Obtain the Key Item [b][color=#F7D58B]Avatar phantom gem[/color][/b] (Merit Cost: 10).
                            • [b][color=#66ccff]Odnowa Earring +1:[/color][/b] Provides Magic Damage Taken -2% and Damage Taken -3%.
                            • [b][color=#66ccff]Priwen:[/color][/b] Obtainable by trading materials to [b][color=#F7D58B]Oboro[/color][/b] in Port Jeuno (E-6).
                            • [b][color=#66ccff]Nixxer:[/color][/b] Purchased from [b][color=#F7D58B]Zurim[/color][/b] in Norg for 200 Domain Points.
                            • [b][color=#66ccff]Twilight Torque:[/color][/b] Dropped by [b][color=#F7D58B]Shinryu[/color][/b] in the final Abyssea scenario fight.
                            
                            This setup significantly enhances defensive capabilities with improved damage reduction and stats compared to basic gear. Note: The Magic Damage Taken (MDT) at -47% is not an issue since any Shell spell will cap MDT at -50%.
                        [/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table][div align="center"][table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse; padding:5px; margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px; line-height:1.8; box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 12px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); border-radius:25px; overflow:hidden;"]
                        [tr style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);"][td style="text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; width:130px;"][itemset]397651[/itemset][/td]
                            [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; white-space:nowrap;"][div style="text-align:left; display:inline-block; line-height:1.5;"][size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]PDT: -60% (Cap -50%)[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]MDT: -47% (Capped at -50% with Shell)[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Enmity: +21[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]VIT: +194[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]DEF: +702[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]HP: +315[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Evasion: +294[/color][/b][/size]
                                    [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Def. Bonus: +10%[/color][/b][/size]
                                [/div]
                            [/td]
                            [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:0 10px 0 10px; vertical-align:middle;"][size=14]An improved defensive set built from Ambuscade and mid-tier items, providing superior mitigation for a developing [b][color=#F7D58B]99 PLD[/color][/b].[/size]
                            [/td]
                        [/tr]
                    [/table][/div][/div]

            [div id="section-idle-mid-pdt" style="
            margin:10px auto; 
            background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
            padding:10px; 
            border-radius:10px; 
            border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); 
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  
            color:#E0E0E0; 
            font-size:14px;
            text-align:left;"]
                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]Mid-Tier Idle Set[/color]
                    [url=#section-idle-sets style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url]
                [/div]
                [table width="100%"]
                    [tr]
                        [td style="color:#ffffff; line-height:2; font-size:14px; padding:10px;"]
                            This set is a highly effective and practical solution for Paladins seeking a durable and accessible defensive build. It serves as a fully viable option even before transitioning to more advanced gear.

                            [b][color=#F7D58B]Important Notes:[/color][/b]
                            • This setup fully utilizes the [color=#66ccff]Sakpata's[/color] gear set, renowned for its strong defensive stats and ease of acquisition compared to more demanding sets like [color=#66ccff]Sulevia's +2[/color] or the very expensive [color=#66ccff]Souveran +1[/color].
                            • The [color=#66ccff]Sakpata's[/color] set is more accessible, especially with the help of experienced players, and offers stats that remain effective even in high-end content.
                            • In contrast, the [color=#66ccff]Sulevia's +2[/color] set is time-consuming to obtain and often becomes obsolete in advanced builds, while the [color=#66ccff]Souveran +1[/color] set, though effective, is costly and can result in an excessively high HP pool (~3600) for idle situations.
                            • This build achieves a balanced [color=#7fe07f]HP pool (~3200)[/color] while maintaining capped [color=#F7D58B]-50%[/color] [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color].
                            • Key components include [color=#66ccff]Brilliance[/color] as the weapon, [color=#66ccff]Eluder's Sachet[/color] as ammo, and rings like [color=#66ccff]Provocare Ring[/color] and [color=#66ccff]Gelatinous Ring +1[/color] to maximize survivability and enmity.

                            This setup offers Paladins a solid foundation for tanking, providing a dependable intermediate solution that remains effective well into high-tier content.
                        [/td]
                    [/tr]
                [/table]
                [div align="center"][table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse; padding:5px; margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px; line-height:1.8; box-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 4px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1), 0 0 12px rgba(255, 223, 128, 1); border-radius:25px; overflow:hidden;"]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);"]
                        [td style="text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; width:130px;"]
                            [itemset]397653[/itemset]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:10px; vertical-align:middle; white-space:nowrap;"][div style="text-align:left; display:inline-block; line-height:1.5;"][size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]• PDT: -76% (Cap -50%)[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]MDT: -60% (Cap -50%)[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Enmity: +34[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]VIT: +233[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]DEF: +1413[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]HP: +1063[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Evasion: +754[/color][/b][/size]
                                [size=14]• [b][color=#F7D58B]Magic Def. Bonus: +30[/color][/b][/size]
                            [/div]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding:0 10px 0 10px; vertical-align:middle;"][size=14]This intermediate defensive set provides a robust balance of damage mitigation, Enmity management, and survivability. It has evolved from prior setups to incorporate more versatile and specialized items while maintaining core defensive capabilities.[/size][/td][/tr][/table][/div]
