                [div align="center" style="text-align:center; font-size:25px; margin-bottom:15px;"][color=#cea425]JAs Sets
                    [url=#section-enmity-sets style="font-size:14px;"][color=#2980B9]▲ Back to top ▲[/color][/url][/div]
                    [table][tr][td style="color:#E0E0E0; line-height:2; font-size:14px; padding:10px;"][color=#66ccff]Job Ability (JA) Sets[/color] are built upon the [color=#66ccff]Full Enmity Set[/color], with specific gear pieces swapped in to enhance each [color=#e5d522]Job Ability[/color]. The foundation focuses on maximizing [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color], but using [color=#F7D58B]+3[/color] versions of gear is recommended for the improved [color=#F7D58B]DEF[/color], [color=#F7D58B]VIT[/color], [color=#7fe07f]HP[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] stats. While JA-specific bonuses are identical across NQ, +1, +2, and +3 versions, the extra defensive stats from +3 gear enhance survivability—especially valuable even for the short activation time of JAs.

                            • [color=#F7D58B]Optimized for JAs[/color]: Focuses on maximizing [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] while enhancing the selected Job Ability.  
                            • [color=#F7D58B]+3 Gear Upgrade[/color]: Significantly boosts [color=#F7D58B]DEF[/color], [color=#F7D58B]VIT[/color], [color=#7fe07f]HP[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] for better durability.  
                            • [color=#F7D58B]Flexible Setup[/color]: Swap only the necessary gear pieces to support the JA without sacrificing defense.

                            Below is an example of the [color=#66ccff]Full Enmity Set[/color] followed by a detailed table listing each [color=#e5d522]Job Ability[/color] with the recommended gear to maximize its effect.
                        [/td][/tr]
