                    [table][tr][td style="color:#E0E0E0; line-height:2; font-size:14px; padding:10px;"][color=#66ccff]Engaged XP Set[/color] This set is identical to the [color=#66ccff]Idle XP Set[/color], with one key exception: the weapon is switched to [color=#66ccff]Malevolence[/color].  

                                The reason for maintaining a tanky setup instead of switching to a DPS-focused one is the high frequency of incoming attacks when leveling at [color=#F7D58B]Crawler's Nest [S][/color]. These constant hits ensure you quickly regain 3000 TP after each Weaponskill, making a defensive approach more efficient.  

                                [b]Key Features:[/b]
                                • Full tanky setup to handle the high number of incoming attacks.  
                                • Retains strong [color=#F7D58B]PDT/MDT/DT[/color] reductions for reliable survivability.  
                                • Optimized for frequent hits, allowing consistent performance in combat.  

                                [b]Usage:[/b]
                                Stick to the defensive setup from the Idle XP set and switch to [color=#66ccff]Malevolence[/color] for improved adaptability in high-hit scenarios.
                        [/td][/tr]
